      <div xml:id="NA59-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu viṉaimuṟṟi mīḷvāṉ tērppākaṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is what he who returned after completing [his] work said to the charioteer.</p>
      </div>
      <div xml:id="NA59">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            uṭumpu kolīi varinuṇa lakaḻntu</l>
<l>            neṭuṅkōṭṭup puṟṟat tīyal keṇṭi</l>
<l>            yellumuya leṟinta vēṭṭuva ṉañcuvala</l>
<l>            palvēṟu paṇṭat toṭaimaṟan tillat </l>
<l rend="indent4">añcuval koṇṭa toṭaituṟan tillat</l>
<l>            tirumaṭaik kaḷḷi ṉiṉkaḷi cerukkum </l>
<l>            vaṉpulak kāṭṭunāṭ ṭatuvē yaṉpukalantu</l>
<l>            namvayiṟ purinta koḷkaiyoṭu neñcat</l>
<l>            tuḷḷiṉa ḷuṟaivō ḷūrē mullai</l>
<l>            nuṇmukai yaviḻnta puṟaviṟ</l>
<l>            poṟaitalai maṇantaṉ ṟuyavumā riṉiyē.</l>
            </lg>
       <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>It [lies] in a land of wilderness with hard soil,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the hunter, who had killed the iguana, excavated(?) the frog,</l>
<l rend="indent2">dug white ants from the long-peaked anthill</l>
<l rend="indent2">[and] thrown down the hare even at night(?), forgets the bundle</l>
<l rend="indent">of many different stores on [his] pretty shoulder</l>
<l rend="indent">[and] is elated by sweet intoxication with toddy at a great drinking,</l>
<l>– the village where she remains [and] remembers</l>
<l rend="indent">in [her] heart with the doctrine<note place="foot">The use of the word <term xml:lang="ta">koḷkai</term> in this context is slightly disconcerting, unless it is meant to refer to HER right (and obligation) to think of HIM as a wedded wife; moreover the locative mark on <term xml:lang="ta">namvayiṉ</term> is unusual, since <term xml:lang="ta">purinta</term> should go with a direct object.</note> of desiring us, mingling in love.</l>
<l rend="indent3">Now,</l>
<l rend="indent">in the woodland where fine buds have opened on the jasmine,</l>
<l>patience has been entangled with suffering.</l>
        </lg>
